news.title: Macrotech Developers buys 2.8 acres in Pune's Hinjewadi from Paranjape Schemes
news.para: The land parcel was mortgaged by Paranjape Realty Spaces, a group entity of the seller, to avail a loan from ASK Real Estate Special Opportunities Fund II and III managed by ASK Properties Investment Advisors.

news.title: Gurugram: M3M Soulitude buyers accuse builder of unethical practices
news.para: The investors, predominantly from middle-income households, participated in a 10:90 payment scheme in Nov 2021, anticipating handover of their dream homes. Currently, they assert that M3M has not fulfilled its contractual obligations as the project approaches completion.

news.title: Ambuja Cements seeks CCI nod to acquire majority stake in Orient Cement
news.para: ​According to a CCI notice, the proposed transaction is a two-stage acquisition process, initiated through two share purchase agreements (SPAs) on October 22, 2024, will see Ambuja Cements initially acquiring a 46.80 per cent stake in Orient Cement.

news.title: Bhutani Infra acquires Logix City Center in Noida for around Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: "We have acquired Logix City Center from PAG and Logix group promoters. The total investment will be Rs 1,000 crore, including the acquisition cost and renovations," Bhutani Infra CEO Ashish Bhutani told PTI.

news.title: The Ramco Cements' net profit dips 64.21% in Q2 FY25
news.para: The Ramco Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,053.94 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 12.68 per cent from Rs 2,352.09 crore it reported in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shree Cement posts net profit of Rs 76.64 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Shree Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,235.55 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 13.66 per cent from Rs 4,905.62 crore it reported in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Brick kilns in Punjab contaminate water with toxic metals: Study
news.para: As per the study, these kilns are major sources of heavy metal pollution, largely due to the burning of coal and other fuels in brick production. The findings underscore an urgent need for stricter regulations, including promoting biomass as a cleaner alternative to the vast amounts of coal.

news.title: MPIDC to invest over Rs 200 crore in three industrial zones in Mandsaur
news.para: New industrial zones Maksi, Shajapur and Jaggakhedi in Mandsaur district are slated to be developed in FY 2025.

news.title: Commercial property prices in Germany drop 4.7% in Q3 2024
news.para: It was the second consecutive quarter-on-quarter rise but it is still too early to sound the all-clear, VDP said. Prices may move sideways in the coming quarters, and further setbacks are possible given a weak economy and geopolitical risks.

news.title: Gujarat government to enforce new liquid waste management rules for societies
news.para: ​​The new rules will have significant implications for residential societies, both existing and newly constructed, as they introduce stringent requirements for wastewater treatment and reuse.

news.title: Keystone Realtors posts net profit of Rs 65.55 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Keystone Realtors' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 556.22 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 12.18 per cent from Rs 633.33 crore it reported in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nashik: Two booked for cheating villa owner of Rs 76,000
news.para: The official from the Trambakeshwar police station said that complainant Aniruddh Powar owns a property - Mountain Mist Villa - in Nashik Rural and rents it out to holidayers. Police identified the accused as Chinmay Mungi and Abhishek Vidawat.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government issues guidelines to CRDA on Amaravati development project
news.para: The state govt listed its priorities regarding various infrastructure works in Amaravati to be taken up with the loan to be granted by World Bank and Asian Development Bank (ADB). The state govt appointed CRDA as nodal agency to deal with WB and ADB and take up developmental activities in Amaravati.

news.title: Aparna Constructions invests Rs 2,851 crore to develop first phase of township in Hyderabad
news.para: This 123-acre township comprises of high-rise apartment communities and a gated community of 99 independent bungalows.

news.title: Karnataka HC grants relief to BDA, stays 2012 order on Kengeri property dispute
news.para: While directing BDA to pay Rs 25,000 in cost, Justice ES Indiresh has now scheduled the review petition for Nov 25 for further consideration. The cost is payable to R Arunachalam, the original petitioner.

news.title: Bengaluru: Flat owner associations raise concerns over BBMP's e-khata system for apartments
news.para: E-khatas are geotagged but stacked flats share the same coordinates, making it challenging to verify individual compliance with building plans.

news.title: Chennai: Illegal sand dune mining in Injambakkam beach threatens coastline
news.para: In May, the National Green Tribunal prohibited CMDA from disturbing dunes on Injambakkam beach, mandating permissions from Union govt or State Coastal Zone Management Authority.

news.title: Gurugram: RWAs warned of deregistration over audit non-compliance
news.para: Under the HRRS Act, societies are required to submit a balance sheet, a statement of receipts and expenditures, and an auditor's report.

news.title: State owned banks explore new route to home loan evaluation for informal sector
news.para: Different from the regular disbursement under ‘affordable housing’ programmes, this proposal would aim at assessing borrowers’ earnings in alternative ways — like considering transaction levels of a street vendor from his QR code credits.

news.title: MCZMA orders probe into alleged CRZ violations in PMAY housing projects in Navi Mumbai
news.para: The action was initiated following a complaint by NatConnect Foundation on the PMO Public Grievance website, claiming that PMAY projects, particularly in the Mansarovar and Kharghar areas, were built near mangroves, mudflats, and inter-tidal wetlands.
